    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9200, 9300, 9400 Models Built After January 1, 1995 - ELECTRICAL
        TROUBLESHOOTING CAB ACCESSORIES - TROUBLESHOOTING - Heated Mirrors With Right Motorized Mirror
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Heated Mirrors With Right Motorized Mirror</title>
        <table id="t0805309" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Testing Heated Mirrors</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="1.80in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="1.80in"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="7" spanname="1to7"/>
                <thead valign="bottom">
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="7" spanname="1to7" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TESTING HEATED MIRRORS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Check 10A fuse F5-A for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>F5-A.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off/On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Disconnect connector (483) from mirror switch. Turn key ON. At connector (483) measure
                                voltage to gnd. at circuit 78.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>(438) 78 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>12&#177;1.5 volts?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 78 from fuse, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>With switch in ON position measure resistance between terminals 5 and 6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Mirror switch, 5 to 6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Replace the switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>With switch in OFF position measure resistance between terminals 5 and 6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Mirror switch, 5 to 6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>>100K ohm?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Replace the switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Use diode test feature of fluke meter to test the LEDs in the switch if they are not
                                operating.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off/On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Connect the switch to connector (438). Turn key ON. With mirror switch ON, at
                                connector (70) measure voltage to gnd. at circuit 78A (right) or 78B (left).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>(70) 78A or 78B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>12&#177;1.5 volts?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit between switch and connector (70), then
                                repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>With heated mirror switch ON, at connector (70) measure voltage between circuits 78A
                                and 11-GY.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>(70) 78A to 11GY.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>12&#177;1.5 volts?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Replace heater element.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 11-GY path to gnd., then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
        <table id="t0805310" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Testing Motorized Mirror</title>
